Why this exists
---------------

Distributing a binary through the Apple App Store (and through TestFlight)
requires agreeing to Apple's Licensed Application End User License Agreement
and App Store terms. Those terms place conditions on end users and on
distribution (for example limits on the number of devices, digital-rights-
management and anti-circumvention rules, and other usage restrictions) that
conflict with the AGPL's sections 6, 7, and 10 (which forbid imposing further
restrictions on the rights the license grants). This is the well-known
"GPL on the App Store" conflict. Because Silva Peak Labs, LLC is the copyright
holder, it can resolve the conflict for its own distribution by granting the
additional permission below. Anyone else redistributing NorthKeep through an
app store would need their own grant or their own copyright basis.


The grant
---------

